In the case of COVID-19 they changed the designation from epidemic to pandemic on March 11th, 2020.

But while it's contained in that area, a disease is considered an epidemic. A pandemic is larger, this word is used when a disease has spread globally. Originally COVID-19 was focussed in Asia, and it was called an epidemic.

Also, remember that COVID-19 is the name of the disease, not the virus itself. The virus that causes COVID-19 is actually "SARS-CoV-2". Other confusing words we're hearing a lot in relation to COVID-19 are epidemic and pandemic.
